text: Texas's 30th congressional district of the United States House of Representatives covers much of the city of Dallas and other parts of Dallas and Tarrant counties. The 30th district is also home to Dallas Love Field airport and University of Texas Southwestern Medical Center. The current Representative from the 30th district is Democrat Jasmine Crockett, who has represented the district since 2023. She replaced longtime representative Eddie Bernice Johnson, who was first elected in 1993. ==References== Category:Congressional districts of Texas
